All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractBaseMapCrudService<T extends AbstractBaseObject>
The AbstractBaseMapCrudService is an abstract class extending the AbstractMapCrudService and providing additional functionality for managing AbstractBaseObject entities.
AbstractBaseObject
The AbstractBaseObject is an abstract class providing a base structure for objects with a unique identifier (id) and a name.
AbstractBeanStatusService
The AbstractBeanStatusService class is an abstract service providing functionality for managing the status of biogeochemical species beans in the PANDORA model.
AbstractHashMapService
The AbstractHashMapService is an abstract class providing common functionality for services that utilize a hash map to store data based on the combination of a Cell and a LocalDateTime.
AbstractMapCrudService<T,ID>
The AbstractMapCrudService is an abstract class implementing the CrudService interface for managing entities using a Map as the underlying storage.
AqueousSpecie
The AqueousSpecie abstract class extends the Specie class and provides a concrete implementation of the SpecieLogic interface by overriding the AqueousSpecie.calculateTransport(double, double) method.
Carbon
The Carbon interface represents a carbon-based chemical entity in PANDORA chemistry.
Cell
The Cell class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a geographical cell with a unique identifier, name, and additional properties such as center latitude, center longitude, surface area, and the identifier of the next cell in the sequence.
CellMapCrudService
CellMapCrudService is an implementation of the AbstractBaseMapCrudService class, providing CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing Cell objects.
CellTimestep
The CellTimestep class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a specific time step associated with a geographical cell.
CellTimestepMapCrudService
CellTimestepMapCrudService is an implementation of the AbstractBaseMapCrudService class, providing CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing CellTimestep objects.
CellTimestepService
The CellTimestepService interface defines methods for calculating the time series of cell timesteps for a given geographical cell.
CellTimestepServiceImpl
The CellTimestepServiceImpl class implements the CellTimestepService interface and provides functionality for calculating the time series of cell timesteps in the Pandora model.
CrudService<T,ID>
The CrudService interface defines generic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing entities of type T with identifiers of type ID.
DIC
The DIC class represents Dissolved Inorganic Carbon (DIC) as a bean in the PANDORA model.
DicBeanStatusService
The DicBeanStatusService class is a service responsible for managing the status of the Dissolved Inorganic Carbon (DIC) bean in the PANDORA model.
DischargesMapService
The DischargesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing discharge values associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
DischargesMapServiceImpl
DischargesMapServiceImpl is an implementation of the DischargesMapService interface, providing services related to managing discharge values associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
Dissolved
The Dissolved interface represents a dissolved chemical entity in PANDORA chemistry.
DOC
The DOC class represents Dissolved Organic Carbon (DOC) as a bean in the PANDORA model.
DocBeanStatusService
The DocBeanStatusService class is a service responsible for managing the status of the Dissolved Organic Carbon (DOC) bean in the PANDORA model.
ErosionLogic
The ErosionLogic interface defines a method for calculating the sediment transport coefficient based on specified erosion-related parameters.
ErosionLogicImpl
The ErosionLogicImpl class is an implementation of the ErosionLogic interface, providing a method to calculate the sediment transport coefficient based on specified parameters.
FirstOrderDifferentialEquationsService
The FirstOrderDifferentialEquationsService interface defines a method for creating and returning a set of first-order differential equations for the Pandora model based on the provided PandoraTimestep.
FirstOrderDifferentialEquationsServiceImpl
The FirstOrderDifferentialEquationsServiceImpl class implements the FirstOrderDifferentialEquationsService interface and provides functionality for creating a set of first-order differential equations for the Pandora model.
Inorganic
The Inorganic interface represents an inorganic chemical entity in PANDORA chemistry.
IntegratorConfiguration
The IntegratorConfiguration class is a Spring configuration class responsible for creating and configuring the numerical integrator bean used in the PANDORA model simulation.
LocalDateTimeService
The LocalDateTimeService interface defines methods for performing operations related to LocalDateTime instances in the context of the Pandora model.
LocalDateTimeServiceImpl
The LocalDateTimeServiceImpl class implements the LocalDateTimeService interface and provides functionality for working with LocalDateTime instances in the Pandora model.
MapService
The MapService interface defines a common method for cleaning or resetting the map managed by the service.
Organic
The Organic interface represents an organic chemical entity in PANDORA chemistry, and it defines a method to retrieve the oxidation rate associated with this organic species.
Oxidation<T extends Organic>
The Oxidation class represents an abstract implementation of the OxidationConfiguration interface, providing common functionality for configuring oxidation reactions in freshwater systems.
OxidationConfiguration
The OxidationConfiguration interface extends the ReactionConfiguration interface and represents the configuration of oxidation reactions in freshwater systems.
OxidationDoc
Configuration class for oxidation reactions involving Dissolved Organic Carbon (DOC) species.
PandoraDifferentialEquations
The PandoraDifferentialEquations class implements the FirstOrderDifferentialEquations interface and represents the differential equations governing the Pandora model for a specific time step.
PandoraIntegratorService
The PandoraIntegratorService interface defines a method for integrating the Pandora model simulation for a given PandoraTimestep.
PandoraIntegratorServiceImpl
The PandoraIntegratorServiceImpl class implements the PandoraIntegratorService interface and provides functionality for integrating the Pandora model simulation for a given PandoraTimestep.
PandoraTimestep
The PandoraTimestep class represents a specific time step in the Pandora model, characterized by initial values, start and end times, dimensionality, discharge, volume, terrestrial and upstream sources, and other properties.
PandoraTimestepBuilder
The PandoraTimestepBuilder class is a builder for creating instances of PandoraTimestep.
Particle
The Particle interface defines methods to retrieve information about a particle, including its radius and density.
ParticulateSpecieBean
The ParticulateSpecieBean class is an abstract class representing a particulate species with properties related to particle physics.
Reaction
The Reaction class represents an abstract implementation of the ReactionConfiguration interface, providing common functionality for configuring biogeochemical reactions in freshwater systems.
ReactionCalculationService
The ReactionCalculationService interface defines a method for calculating reactions in the Pandora model based on the current state variables.
ReactionCalculationServiceImpl
The ReactionCalculationServiceImpl class implements the ReactionCalculationService interface and provides functionality for calculating reactions in the Pandora model based on the current state variables.
ReactionConfiguration
The ReactionConfiguration interface represents the configuration of a biogeochemical reaction in freshwater systems.
ReactionConfigurationBeanService
The ReactionConfigurationBeanService interface defines methods for managing and retrieving ReactionConfiguration instances within the application.
ReactionConfigurationBeanServiceImpl
The ReactionConfigurationBeanServiceImpl service class provides methods for managing and retrieving ReactionConfiguration instances within the application.
River
The River class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a river entity characterized by a unique identifier, name, and a list of independent cell sets associated with the river.
RiverMapCrudService
RiverMapCrudService is an implementation of the AbstractBaseMapCrudService class, providing CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing River objects.
RiverTimestep
The RiverTimestep class extends AbstractBaseObject and represents a river timestep entity with a unique identifier, name, and a list of independent cell timesteps associated with the river timestep.
RiverTimestepMapCrudService
RiverTimestepMapCrudService is an implementation of the AbstractBaseMapCrudService class, providing CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing RiverTimestep objects.
RiverTimestepService
The RiverTimestepService interface defines a method for calculating the next timestep for each cell in the river simulation.
RiverTimestepServiceImpl
The RiverTimestepServiceImpl class implements the RiverTimestepService interface and provides functionality for calculating the next timestep for each cell within a river simulation.
Sediment
The Sediment interface defines methods for obtaining properties of sediment particles, including radius, density, and characteristics relevant to sediment transport.
SedimentarySpecie
The SedimentarySpecie abstract class extends the Specie class and provides a concrete implementation of the SpecieLogic interface by overriding the SedimentarySpecie.calculateTransport(double, double) method.
SedimentSpecieBean
The SedimentSpecieBean class is an abstract class representing a sediment species with properties related to sediment physics.
ShearStressLogic
The ShearStressLogic interface defines methods for calculating shear stress, critical shear stress for sediment transport, and the Shields parameter based on specified parameters.
ShearStressLogicImpl
The ShearStressLogicImpl class is an implementation of the ShearStressLogic interface, providing methods to calculate shear stress, critical shear stress for sediment transport, and the Shields parameter based on specified parameters.
Specie
The Specie abstract class extends the Variable class and implements both the SpecieConfiguration and SpecieLogic interfaces.
SpecieBeanService
The SpecieBeanService interface defines methods for managing and retrieving Specie instances within the application.
SpecieBeanServiceImpl
The SpecieBeanServiceImpl service class provides methods for managing and retrieving Specie instances within the application.
SpecieConfiguration
The SpecieConfiguration interface extends the VariableConfiguration interface and provides an additional method for retrieving the molar mass of the biogeochemical species.
SpecieLogic
The SpecieLogic interface defines methods for calculating the transport of a biogeochemical species in the freshwater system.
SpecieStatusService
The SpecieStatusService interface defines methods for checking and toggling the status of biogeochemical species beans in the PANDORA model.
TerrestrialSourcesMapService
The TerrestrialSourcesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing terrestrial sources data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
TerrestrialSourcesMapServiceImpl
TerrestrialSourcesMapServiceImpl is an implementation of the TerrestrialSourcesMapService interface, providing services related to managing terrestrial sources data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
TransportCalculationService
The TransportCalculationService interface defines a method for calculating the transport of each species based on the given state variables and discharge rate.
TransportCalculationServiceImpl
The TransportCalculationServiceImpl class implements the TransportCalculationService interface and provides functionality for calculating the transport of each species based on the given state variables and discharge rate.
UpstreamSourcesMapService
The UpstreamSourcesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing upstream sources data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
UpstreamSourcesMapServiceImpl
UpstreamSourcesMapServiceImpl is an implementation of the UpstreamSourcesMapService interface, providing services related to managing upstream sources data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
Variable
The Variable class is an abstract implementation of the VariableConfiguration interface, providing basic functionality for a variable within the PANDORA model.
VariableConfiguration
The VariableConfiguration interface represents a configuration for a variable within the PANDORA model.
VolumesMapService
The VolumesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing volume data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
VolumesMapServiceImpl
VolumesMapServiceImpl is an implementation of the VolumesMapService interface, providing services related to managing volume data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
YMapService
The YMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing state variable data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
YMapServiceImpl
YMapServiceImpl is an implementation of the YMapService interface, providing services related to managing state variable data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
